"turning off on the left. Take this lane for about & € third of a mile, till, where it makes a decided bend tothe left, you see in front of you, and just beyond a swing-gate on the right, a field-gate admitting to a foot-path. Take this path for a full mile, passing over a branch of the Midland Railway by a level crossing, and emerging by a short lane into a traffic road. There turn to the right, and follow the road straight for a mile to the bridge over the old chan- nel of the Brent. Thence go on up the hill a full quarter of & mile to the first turning on the left (to Wembley). Follow this picturesque road (Forty Lane) for a good mile and a half, till you come to the cross-roads above Wembley. There—"